# ğŸ–ï¸ Visual SoundPad

A computer vision-controlled soundpad. You make hand gestures (1 to 5 fingers), and audio plays through your microphone for your friends to hear.

## ğŸš€ Installation

### 1. Required Software
* Python (3.10 or 3.11 recommended)
* VoiceMeeter Banana (To mix the audio): https://vb-audio.com/Voicemeeter/banana.htm

### 2. Install Libraries
Open the terminal in the project folder and run:
pip install -r requirements.txt

---

## ğŸ›ï¸ Audio Setup (Crucial!)

To ensure audio goes to Discord without echo or stuttering, configure VoiceMeeter Banana exactly like this:

### In VoiceMeeter Banana:
1. Hardware Out A1 (Top Right Corner): Select your main Headphones (prefer WDM drivers).
2. Hardware Input 1 (Your Microphone):
   - Enable only **B1** (Sends your voice to Discord).
   - Disable **A1** (So you don't hear yourself).
3. Voicemeeter Input (Virtual - PC/Game Sounds):
   - Enable only **A1** (So you hear the game).
   - Disable **B1** (So game audio doesn't leak into the mic).
4. Voicemeeter AUX (Virtual - Where the Soundpad plays):
   - Enable **A1** (So you hear the sound effect).
   - Enable **B1** (So your friends hear the sound effect).

### In Windows:
- Click the sound icon and select as default output: **VoiceMeeter Input (VB-Audio VoiceMeeter VAIO)**.
- This ensures PC audio goes to the middle column of VoiceMeeter.

### âš ï¸ Important (Anti-Robot Voice):
Ensure both VoiceMeeter and Windows are set to **48000Hz**.
- VoiceMeeter: Menu > System Settings > Preferred SampleRate: 48000Hz.
- Windows: Old Sound Panel (mmsys.cpl) > Recording/Playback > Properties > Advanced > 48000Hz.

---

## ğŸ§ Discord Setup

For your friends to hear high-quality audio:

1. Input Device: Change to **VoiceMeeter Output (VB-Audio VoiceMeeter VAIO)**.
2. Turn off Filters: Go to *Voice & Video* and disable:
   - Noise Suppression (Krisp/Standard) -> Set to "None".
   - Echo Cancellation -> Off.
   - Noise Reduction -> Off.

---

## ğŸ•¹ï¸ How to Use

1. Run the script: python app.py
2. Click the folder icons ğŸ“‚ to select your audio files (MP3/WAV).
3. Click START CAMERA.
4. Make the gesture (e.g., 2 fingers) and hold for 1 second until the bar fills up.

Enjoy!